Study_Name: Mason County Stormwater Management Program Water Quality Monitoring Plan
Study_Purpose: Project Objectives include: 1)Survey stormwater outfalls in Mason County. 2) Gather data to help characterize stormwater problems and sources, including monitoring results of both wet-weather stormwater flows and dry weather base-flows. 3) Provide a baseline for comparison with future data. 4) Assess impacts of stormwater discharge to be used for prioritization of facility creation or retrofit. 5) Provide the above data to aid in stormwater management planning. 6) Gather data to evaluate the effectiveness of the SWM program, for the purpose of adaptive management.
Ecology_Program_or_Other_Responsible_Ent: Ecy Water Quality Program, Southwest Region
Submitting_Organization: Mason County Public Health - Environmental Health
Study_QA_Assessment_Level: Level 4:  Data Verified and Assessed for Usability in a Formal Study Report
